text: The Zanesville YMCA, at 34 S. Fifth St. in Zanesville, Ohio, was built in 1919. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1985. It was designed by architect Cyrus McLane and built by the Lorenz Construction Co. McLane was architect of the Rock Island YMCA, in Rock Island, Illinois, and of other YMCA buildings. Site of former building The building has been destroyed. ==See also== *Zanesville YWCA, also NRHP-listed ==References== ==External links== *Muskingum Family YMCA, 1861 Adams Lane, current website Category:YMCA buildings in the United States Category:National Register of Historic Places in Muskingum County, Ohio Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1919
